OL,3,COne in five struggled to pay water
OL,4,Cbill in last year ` Citizens Advice
OL,6,FThe survey, taken at the beginning of
OL,7,FAugust, and following the largest
OL,8,Fsingle-year increase in household
OL,9,Fwater charges since privatisation of
OL,10,Fthe industry, found that more than two
OL,11,Ffifths (42%) of those finding it hard
OL,12,Fto keep pace with their bills had been
OL,13,Fforced to cut back on groceries and
OL,14,Fenergy as a result.
OL,16,FOver a third of those struggling (35%)
OL,17,Fwere rationing water, including by
OL,18,Fcutting showers, toilet flushes and
OL,19,Fclothes washing.
